<TITLE> Ban Ki-moon lauds emergency lift </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com)UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon has welcomed the lifting of emergency ahead of the Bangladesh elections, says an adviser. Ban termed the decision a "positive step" for holding a free, fair and credible parliamentary election, foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury said Thursday. "The UN secretary-general made an announcement in New York hailing the withdrawal of the state of emergency in Bangladesh," Iftekhar told bdnews24.com at his office. He said a high-level panel of the secretary-general, headed by Francesc Vendrell, would return to Bangladesh next week to assess and report on the preparations for the elections and post-election transition. During his Dhaka visit on Nov 1, Ban Ki-moon urged the interim government to lift the state of emergency for free and fair polls. He also sent the delegation headed by Vendrell to do a primary assessment on the political situation in Bangladesh during the run-up to elections. The team submitted a report to the secretary-general terming the environment "election-friendly". bdn
